  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Besides the specific response to vaccine antigens, the investigators will analyze the
      anti-HPV immune response in HIV-1-infected men in different strata of immune deficiency. The
      hypothesis will be tested by stratification by T CD4 + lymphocytes in an attempt to assess
      the range of the count with the highest possibility of vaccine response. Thus, knowledge of
      vaccine response in HIV-infected patients, indicate which patients would have greater
      potential for vaccine response in vivo.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      The study will be divided into three groups. Patients with HIV-1 infection will be subdivided
      into groups according to T CD4 + lymphocytes at the time of vaccination: Over 500 CD4 T cells
      count and bellow 500 CD4 T cells count. A healthy control group will be also studied.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
